# Jac ML Studio — production environment file.
#
# Install to /etc/jac-studio/env (referenced by deploy/studio.service) and lock it down:
#   sudo install -D -m 600 -o root -g root deploy/env.example /etc/jac-studio/env
#   sudo $EDITOR /etc/jac-studio/env      # fill in the secrets below, then:
#   sudo chmod 600 /etc/jac-studio/env    # never world/group readable
#
# systemd reads this via EnvironmentFile=; the file MUST be mode 0600 because it
# holds signing/encryption secrets. Never commit a filled-in copy to git.

# --- Required ---------------------------------------------------------------
# JWT signing secret. Long random string. Generate with:  openssl rand -hex 32
# Doubles as the master key for secret-at-rest encryption (crypto.sv.jac) when
# JAC_SECRET_KEY is unset. Rotating it logs everyone out — see ROTATION below.
JWT_SECRET=

# --- Recommended ------------------------------------------------------------
# Dedicated master key for encrypting stored third-party credentials
# (per-user Vast.ai API keys). Set this so you can rotate the JWT secret WITHOUT
# having to re-enter every user's Vast key. Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
JAC_SECRET_KEY=

# --- Optional: paths (default to the workspace checkout) --------------------
# JAC_STUDIO_WORKSPACE=/opt/jac_ml_studio
# JAC_STUDIO_DATA_ROOT=/opt/jac_ml_studio

# --- Optional: Vast.ai spend guardrails -------------------------------------
# VAST_MAX_CONCURRENT=2          # max simultaneous non-destroyed instances / user
# VAST_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=50       # per-user daily spend ceiling (est. dph*24)
# VAST_MAX_DPH=3.0               # reject any single offer above this $/hr
# Shared fallback key used when a user has not set their own (single-admin deploy):
# VAST_API_KEY=

# --- Optional: job engine ---------------------------------------------------
# JAC_MAX_CONCURRENT_JOBS=4
# JAC_TRASH_DAYS=7
# JAC_API_PORT=8001
# JAC_UI_PORT=8000

# ============================================================================
# SECRET ROTATION
# ============================================================================
# JWT_SECRET
#   Rotating invalidates all issued JWTs -> every user must log in again.
#   1. Generate a new value:  openssl rand -hex 32
#   2. Edit /etc/jac-studio/env, then: sudo systemctl restart jac-studio
#   3. Users re-authenticate. No data is lost (identity is the graph root, not
#      the token).
#   If JAC_SECRET_KEY is UNSET, JWT_SECRET is also the encryption master key, so
#   rotating it makes existing encrypted Vast keys undecryptable (they fail
#   closed; users just re-enter their key). Set JAC_SECRET_KEY to decouple.
#
# JAC_SECRET_KEY (encryption master key)
#   No in-place re-encryption tool ships today. To rotate safely, have each user
#   re-save their Vast key (Settings -> Vast credential) after the new key is
#   live; the next write re-encrypts under the new master. Old ciphertext stops
#   decrypting immediately, so coordinate a window or accept transient failures.
